                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Jiri,\r\nAny comments on this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-09T07:13:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-09T07:13:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47072",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=havlikjiri",
                        "name": "havlikjiri",
                        "displayName": "Jiri Havlik",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Kai,\r\n\r\nmy problem is that it is not possible to remove pages in subcontainers. Eg. page DVD cant be deleted by calling something like $container->removePageByUri(dvd, true); Where \"true\" means Search all containers recursively. You have to get the right container first and then delete your page.\r\n\r\nI think that it would be nice to have a function which searches all containers recursively for page given to delete.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=havlikjiri",
                        "name": "havlikjiri",
                        "displayName": "Jiri Havlik",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-09T07:53:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-09T07:53:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47077",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ah, I understand.\r\n\r\n|findOneBy|removeOneBy|\r\n|findAllBy|removeAllBy|\r\n|findBy|removeBy|\r\n\r\nI think for the implementation, we can use all \"find\" methods.\r\n\r\n{code:title=Example (not tested)}\r\npublic function removeOneBy($property, $value)\r\n{\r\n    $page = $this->findOneBy($property, $value);\r\n    \r\n    if (null !== $page) {\r\n        return $this->removePage($page);\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return false;\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function removeAllBy($property, $value)\r\n{\r\n    $pages = $this->findAllBy($property, $value);\r\n    \r\n    if (false !== empty($pages)) {\r\n        foreach ($pages as $page) {\r\n            $this->removePage($page);\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        return true\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return false;\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic function removeBy($property, $value, $all = false)\r\n{\r\n    if ($all) {\r\n        return $this->removeAllBy($property, $value);\r\n    } else {\r\n        return $this->removeOneBy($property, $value);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI will write some unit test.\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks for your fast feedback!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-09T08:41:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-09T18:19:06.000+0000"
                },
